OL,3,C'My Hijab is not your business':
OL,4,COlympic athletes denounce French
OL,5,Cheadscarf ban
OL,7,FThe IOC clarified that Muslim athletes
OL,8,Ffrom other countries would be allowed
OL,9,Fto wear the Hijab in the Olympic
OL,10,Fvillage and whilst competing, but
OL,11,FFrench athletes were to uphold the
OL,12,F'principle of secularism' and the idea
OL,13,Fof 'absolute neutrality in public
OL,14,Fservices'.
OL,16,FAmnesty International labelled the
OL,17,FHijab ban as "discriminatory" and
OL,18,F"hypocritical" in a report released
OL,19,Fthis month.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
